9#include "llvm/ADT/Triple.h"
10#include "gtest/gtest.h"
11
12using namespace llvm;
13
14namespace {
15
16TEST(TripleTest, BasicParsing) {
17 Triple T;
18
19 T = Triple("");
20 EXPECT_EQ("", T.getArchName().str());
21 EXPECT_EQ("", T.getVendorName().str());
22 EXPECT_EQ("", T.getOSName().str());
23 EXPECT_EQ("", T.getEnvironmentName().str());
24
25 T = Triple("-");
26 EXPECT_EQ("", T.getArchName().str());
27 EXPECT_EQ("", T.getVendorName().str());
28 EXPECT_EQ("", T.getOSName().str());
29 EXPECT_EQ("", T.getEnvironmentName().str());
30
31 T = Triple("--");
32 EXPECT_EQ("", T.getArchName().str());
33 EXPECT_EQ("", T.getVendorName().str());
34 EXPECT_EQ("", T.getOSName().str());
35 EXPECT_EQ("", T.getEnvironmentName().str());
36
37 T = Triple("---");
38 EXPECT_EQ("", T.getArchName().str());
39 EXPECT_EQ("", T.getVendorName().str());
40 EXPECT_EQ("", T.getOSName().str());
41 EXPECT_EQ("", T.getEnvironmentName().str());
42
43 T = Triple("----");
44 EXPECT_EQ("", T.getArchName().str());
45 EXPECT_EQ("", T.getVendorName().str());
46 EXPECT_EQ("", T.getOSName().str());
47 EXPECT_EQ("-", T.getEnvironmentName().str());
48
49 T = Triple("a");
50 EXPECT_EQ("a", T.getArchName().str());
51 EXPECT_EQ("", T.getVendorName().str());
52 EXPECT_EQ("", T.getOSName().str());
53 EXPECT_EQ("", T.getEnvironmentName().str());
54
55 T = Triple("a-b");
56 EXPECT_EQ("a", T.getArchName().str());
57 EXPECT_EQ("b", T.getVendorName().str());
58 EXPECT_EQ("", T.getOSName().str());
59 EXPECT_EQ("", T.getEnvironmentName().str());
60
61 T = Triple("a-b-c");
62 EXPECT_EQ("a", T.getArchName().str());
63 EXPECT_EQ("b", T.getVendorName().str());
64 EXPECT_EQ("c", T.getOSName().str());
65 EXPECT_EQ("", T.getEnvironmentName().str());
66
67 T = Triple("a-b-c-d");
68 EXPECT_EQ("a", T.getArchName().str());
69 EXPECT_EQ("b", T.getVendorName().str());
70 EXPECT_EQ("c", T.getOSName().str());
71 EXPECT_EQ("d", T.getEnvironmentName().str());
72}
73
74TEST(TripleTest, ParsedIDs) {
75 Triple T;
76
77 T = Triple("i386-apple-darwin");
78 EXPECT_EQ(Triple::x86, T.getArch());
79 EXPECT_EQ(Triple::Apple, T.getVendor());
80 EXPECT_EQ(Triple::Darwin, T.getOS());
81 EXPECT_EQ(Triple::UnknownEnvironment, T.getEnvironment());
82
83 T = Triple("i386-pc-elfiamcu");

614static std::string Join(StringRef A, StringRef B, StringRef C) {
615 std::string Str = A;
616 Str += '-';
617 Str += B;
618 Str += '-';
619 Str += C;
620 return Str;
621}
622
623static std::string Join(StringRef A, StringRef B, StringRef C, StringRef D) {
624 std::string Str = A;
625 Str += '-';
626 Str += B;
627 Str += '-';
628 Str += C;
629 Str += '-';
630 Str += D;
631 return Str;
632}

634TEST(TripleTest, Normalization) {
635
636 EXPECT_EQ("unknown", Triple::normalize(""));
637 EXPECT_EQ("unknown-unknown", Triple::normalize("-"));
638 EXPECT_EQ("unknown-unknown-unknown", Triple::normalize("--"));
639 EXPECT_EQ("unknown-unknown-unknown-unknown", Triple::normalize("---"));
640 EXPECT_EQ("unknown-unknown-unknown-unknown-unknown",
641 Triple::normalize("----"));
642
643 EXPECT_EQ("a", Triple::normalize("a"));
644 EXPECT_EQ("a-b", Triple::normalize("a-b"));
645 EXPECT_EQ("a-b-c", Triple::normalize("a-b-c"));
646 EXPECT_EQ("a-b-c-d", Triple::normalize("a-b-c-d"));
647
648 EXPECT_EQ("i386-b-c", Triple::normalize("i386-b-c"));
649 EXPECT_EQ("i386-a-c", Triple::normalize("a-i386-c"));
650 EXPECT_EQ("i386-a-b", Triple::normalize("a-b-i386"));
651 EXPECT_EQ("i386-a-b-c", Triple::normalize("a-b-c-i386"));
652
653 EXPECT_EQ("a-pc-c", Triple::normalize("a-pc-c"));
654 EXPECT_EQ("unknown-pc-b-c", Triple::normalize("pc-b-c"));
655 EXPECT_EQ("a-pc-b", Triple::normalize("a-b-pc"));
656 EXPECT_EQ("a-pc-b-c", Triple::normalize("a-b-c-pc"));
657
658 EXPECT_EQ("a-b-linux", Triple::normalize("a-b-linux"));
659 EXPECT_EQ("unknown-unknown-linux-b-c", Triple::normalize("linux-b-c"));
660 EXPECT_EQ("a-unknown-linux-c", Triple::normalize("a-linux-c"));
661
662 EXPECT_EQ("i386-pc-a", Triple::normalize("a-pc-i386"));
663 EXPECT_EQ("i386-pc-unknown", Triple::normalize("-pc-i386"));
664 EXPECT_EQ("unknown-pc-linux-c", Triple::normalize("linux-pc-c"));
665 EXPECT_EQ("unknown-pc-linux", Triple::normalize("linux-pc-"));
666
667 EXPECT_EQ("i386", Triple::normalize("i386"));
668 EXPECT_EQ("unknown-pc", Triple::normalize("pc"));
669 EXPECT_EQ("unknown-unknown-linux", Triple::normalize("linux"));
670
671 EXPECT_EQ("x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu", Triple::normalize("x86_64-gnu-linux"));
672
673 // Check that normalizing a permutated set of valid components returns a
674 // triple with the unpermuted components.
675 //
676 // We don't check every possible combination. For the set of architectures A,
677 // vendors V, operating systems O, and environments E, that would require |A|
678 // * |V| * |O| * |E| * 4! tests. Instead we check every option for any given
679 // slot and make sure it gets normalized to the correct position from every
680 // permutation. This should cover the core logic while being a tractable
681 // number of tests at (|A| + |V| + |O| + |E|) * 4!.
682 auto FirstArchType = Triple::ArchType(Triple::UnknownArch + 1);
683 auto FirstVendorType = Triple::VendorType(Triple::UnknownVendor + 1);
684 auto FirstOSType = Triple::OSType(Triple::UnknownOS + 1);
685 auto FirstEnvType = Triple::EnvironmentType(Triple::UnknownEnvironment + 1);
686 StringRef InitialC[] = {Triple::getArchTypeName(FirstArchType),
687 Triple::getVendorTypeName(FirstVendorType),
688 Triple::getOSTypeName(FirstOSType),
689 Triple::getEnvironmentTypeName(FirstEnvType)};
690 for (int Arch = FirstArchType; Arch <= Triple::LastArchType; ++Arch) {
691 StringRef C[] = {InitialC[0], InitialC[1], InitialC[2], InitialC[3]};
692 C[0] = Triple::getArchTypeName(Triple::ArchType(Arch));
693 std::string E = Join(C[0], C[1], C[2]);
694 int I[] = {0, 1, 2};
695 do {
696 EXPECT_EQ(E, Triple::normalize(Join(C[I[0]], C[I[1]], C[I[2]])));
697 } while (std::next_permutation(std::begin(I), std::end(I)));
698 std::string F = Join(C[0], C[1], C[2], C[3]);
699 int J[] = {0, 1, 2, 3};
700 do {
701 EXPECT_EQ(F, Triple::normalize(Join(C[J[0]], C[J[1]], C[J[2]], C[J[3]])));
702 } while (std::next_permutation(std::begin(J), std::end(J)));
703 }
704 for (int Vendor = FirstVendorType; Vendor <= Triple::LastVendorType;
705 ++Vendor) {
706 StringRef C[] = {InitialC[0], InitialC[1], InitialC[2], InitialC[3]};
707 C[1] = Triple::getVendorTypeName(Triple::VendorType(Vendor));
708 std::string E = Join(C[0], C[1], C[2]);
709 int I[] = {0, 1, 2};
710 do {
711 EXPECT_EQ(E, Triple::normalize(Join(C[I[0]], C[I[1]], C[I[2]])));
712 } while (std::next_permutation(std::begin(I), std::end(I)));
713 std::string F = Join(C[0], C[1], C[2], C[3]);
714 int J[] = {0, 1, 2, 3};
715 do {
716 EXPECT_EQ(F, Triple::normalize(Join(C[J[0]], C[J[1]], C[J[2]], C[J[3]])));
717 } while (std::next_permutation(std::begin(J), std::end(J)));
718 }
719 for (int OS = FirstOSType; OS <= Triple::LastOSType; ++OS) {
720 if (OS == Triple::Win32)
721 continue;
722 StringRef C[] = {InitialC[0], InitialC[1], InitialC[2], InitialC[3]};
723 C[2] = Triple::getOSTypeName(Triple::OSType(OS));
724 std::string E = Join(C[0], C[1], C[2]);
725 int I[] = {0, 1, 2};
726 do {
727 EXPECT_EQ(E, Triple::normalize(Join(C[I[0]], C[I[1]], C[I[2]])));
728 } while (std::next_permutation(std::begin(I), std::end(I)));
729 std::string F = Join(C[0], C[1], C[2], C[3]);
730 int J[] = {0, 1, 2, 3};
731 do {
732 EXPECT_EQ(F, Triple::normalize(Join(C[J[0]], C[J[1]], C[J[2]], C[J[3]])));
733 } while (std::next_permutation(std::begin(J), std::end(J)));
734 }
735 for (int Env = FirstEnvType; Env <= Triple::LastEnvironmentType; ++Env) {
736 StringRef C[] = {InitialC[0], InitialC[1], InitialC[2], InitialC[3]};
737 C[3] = Triple::getEnvironmentTypeName(Triple::EnvironmentType(Env));
738 std::string F = Join(C[0], C[1], C[2], C[3]);
739 int J[] = {0, 1, 2, 3};
740 do {
741 EXPECT_EQ(F, Triple::normalize(Join(C[J[0]], C[J[1]], C[J[2]], C[J[3]])));
742 } while (std::next_permutation(std::begin(J), std::end(J)));
743 }
744
745 // Various real-world funky triples. The value returned by GCC's config.sub
746 // is given in the comment.
747 EXPECT_EQ("i386-unknown-windows-gnu",
748 Triple::normalize("i386-mingw32")); // i386-pc-mingw32
749 EXPECT_EQ("x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu",
750 Triple::normalize("x86_64-linux-gnu")); // x86_64-pc-linux-gnu
751 EXPECT_EQ("i486-unknown-linux-gnu",
752 Triple::normalize("i486-linux-gnu")); // i486-pc-linux-gnu
753 EXPECT_EQ("i386-redhat-linux",
754 Triple::normalize("i386-redhat-linux")); // i386-redhat-linux-gnu
755 EXPECT_EQ("i686-unknown-linux",
756 Triple::normalize("i686-linux")); // i686-pc-linux-gnu
757 EXPECT_EQ("arm-none-unknown-eabi",
758 Triple::normalize("arm-none-eabi")); // arm-none-eabi
759 EXPECT_EQ("wasm32-unknown-wasi",
760 Triple::normalize("wasm32-wasi")); // wasm32-unknown-wasi
761 EXPECT_EQ("wasm64-unknown-wasi",
762 Triple::normalize("wasm64-wasi")); // wasm64-unknown-wasi
763}
